00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.059
Additional Lender Required
Repairs After The Appraisal

00:00:03.825 --> 00:00:07.884
If your buyer is using an FHA or VA loan,
there is something important to know

00:00:07.964 --> 00:00:09.835
about what can happen after the appraisal.

00:00:11.329 --> 00:00:15.270
Even if the home appraises at the purchase
price, the lender may still require

00:00:15.270 --> 00:00:17.600
certain repairs before the loan can close.

00:00:18.260 --> 00:00:20.589
These are called lender-required repairs.

00:00:21.412 --> 00:00:25.382
With FHA and VA loans, the
appraisal is not only about value.

00:00:26.022 --> 00:00:28.672
The lender also uses it to
confirm the home meets their

00:00:28.672 --> 00:00:30.082
minimum property standards.

00:00:31.322 --> 00:00:34.742
If the appraiser identifies issues
that do not meet those standards,

00:00:35.422 --> 00:00:38.322
the lender can require they be
addressed before approving the loan.

00:00:39.162 --> 00:00:43.062
Common lender-required repairs can
include things like peeling or chipped

00:00:43.062 --> 00:00:48.482
paint, missing handrails, broken windows,
roof issues, or electrical concerns.

00:00:49.032 --> 00:00:51.562
These requests come from
the lender, not the buyer.

00:00:52.112 --> 00:00:56.492
If lender-required repairs are issued,
you generally have a few options.

00:00:56.922 --> 00:01:00.732
You can complete the repairs, offer
a credit if the lender allows it,

00:01:01.062 --> 00:01:04.052
or decide not to move forward,
which could mean losing the buyer.

00:01:04.899 --> 00:01:09.639
It is important to understand that
buyers using FHA or VA loans cannot waive

00:01:09.639 --> 00:01:11.530
these repairs, even if they want to.

00:01:11.950 --> 00:01:13.620
The lender makes the final decision.

00:01:14.812 --> 00:01:18.952
The best way to prepare is to be aware
of your buyer’s loan type and address

00:01:19.072 --> 00:01:21.402
obvious issues early when possible.

00:01:22.282 --> 00:01:26.402
Being prepared helps avoid delays and
keeps the transaction moving forward.

